This paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). It also discusses regularization techniques, which are commonly used in signal processing and optimization (cs.IT). The paper provides a theoretical analysis of the graph Laplacian regularizer, which is a popular method in machine learning and graph theory (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of anisotropic diffusion, which is a common technique in numerical analysis and partial differential equations (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents an iterative algorithm for image denoising, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
